    <title>Regular Sequences On Squares Of Monomial Ideals</title>
    <summary>  We use initially regular sequences that consist of linear sums to explore the
depth of $R/I^2$, when $I$ is a monomial ideal in a polynomial ring $R$. We
give conditions under which these linear sums form regular or initially regular
sequences on $R/I^2$. We then obtain a criterion for when $\depth R/I^2&gt;1$ and
a lower bound on $\depth R/I^2$.
</summary>
